@ad1992 @dwelle @zsviczian
This is a great idea.  One question: Could we combine this hyperlinks PR with #3915?  I think they could dovetail well.  I have been using #3915 in the plugin #2993 for a year now in my teaching to the benefit of students impacted by COVID-19.

If #3915 were not done in conjunction with hyperlinks, I believe significant maintenance of #3915 would be needed to keep teaching with #2993 this semester.

- Could we add an task to the todo list, to support links other then https://?
- From a package integration perspective it would be awesome if we could publish the `redirectToLink` function on the package props similar to `onLibraryChange` and `onPaste`. This looks like a very simple change to implement.
```typescriptt
private redirectToLink = () => {
  window.open(getAbsoluteLink(this.hitLinkElement.link!));
};

Keeping it very simple, I am thinking of something like this
```typescript
private redirectToLink = () => {
  if (this.props.onOpenLink) {
    try {
      this.props.onOpenLink(this.hitLinkElement.link!);
      return;
    } catch (error: any) {
      console.error(error);
    }
  }
  window.open(getAbsoluteLink(this.hitLinkElement.link!));
};
```

